text: I see people everywhere film at 60fps . It does make the image more smooth , but you have to be very careful when filming at a higher frame rate as it can have an impact on when filming in low light. The higher the frame rate the faster the shutter speed needs to be , which means  you need to film at a higher iso just to help compensate for the amount of lighting you use.

text:
First off love the video, it makes me want to go back to Japan (me and my sister went last september for the first time),
A good tip people can also try for the pokemon cafe is checking for cancellations the night before a day you want to go, my sister and I failed to get tickets for both Osaka and Tokyo Pokemon cafes when they were first released but managed to get cancellations really easily the night before we went (the cancellation spots opened at around 10pm the local time the night before the day you want to go) I imagine the ease may change depending on time of year you go and because we got the reservations for Osaka we didn't try the one in tokyo so I can't comment for that one, but we got pretty good seats and the choice of times wasn't too bad either. Just thought Id share for anyone interested.
